### Description

In the file `src/core/BufferGeometry.js`(1071-1085) the `BufferGeometry.normalizeNormals()` method does not check if the `normal` attribute exists before attempting to access it. When called on a geometry without a normal attribute, the method throws a `TypeError: Cannot read property 'count' of undefined`.


### Code

**Current implementation:**
```javascript
normalizeNormals() {

    const normals = this.attributes.normal;

    for ( let i = 0, il = normals.count; i < il; i ++ ) {

        _vector.fromBufferAttribute( normals, i );

        _vector.normalize();

        normals.setXYZ( i, _vector.x, _vector.y, _vector.z );

    }

}
```

## Suggested Fix

Add a check for the existence of the normal attribute before processing:

```javascript
normalizeNormals() {

    const normals = this.attributes.normal;

    if ( normals === undefined ) {
        error( 'BufferGeometry.normalizeNormals(): Geometry does not have a normal attribute.' );
        return;
    }

    for ( let i = 0, il = normals.count; i < il; i ++ ) {

        _vector.fromBufferAttribute( normals, i );

        _vector.normalize();

        normals.setXYZ( i, _vector.x, _vector.y, _vector.z );

    }

}
```

